caption:
After the coronavirus outbreak, we are often confused about adapting to sudden changes. Barcel, founder of Selow Runners, felt the same way. He created Selow Runners as a routine activity during a hard time.

Every Tuesday and Thursday, they hold a morning run and choose the start in a coffee shop and finish in the same place as the way the community supports local business. 

Not only as a routine sport, together, Barcel wanted to spread positivity around the city, he hoped Selow Runner could get bigger than what it is now.

caption:
🎊 ᗩᑎTI ᒪETOY ᒪETOY ᑕᒪᑌᗷ 🎊
Pulang Internal Festival: Seni Melawan Sepi.

Bukan gala dinner. Bukan town hall.
Ini kenduren yang dibungkus glitter dan beat horeg.
Ketika perekonomian seret tapi jiwa pengen goyang, kami nggak cuma diam, kami ngibingzzz. 🪩

Dari pingpong setengah meja sampai fashion show seadanya. Dari literasi yang liar sampai sketsa yang… yah, niatnya mirip.

🎯 Ini bukan absurd, ini strategi!!
Di tengah dunia yang makin pelit bersenang-senang, kami justru upgrade level, bukan untuk gaya, tapi biar tetap bahagia.

📍 Lokasi: sini-sini aja, tapi rasanya kaya dimana-mana
💸 HTM: cukup bawa niat & napas panjang

Yang penting: rame, absurd, dan sedikit mengguncang iman.

#AntiLetoyLetoyClub
#BukanPestaBiasa
#LowBudgetHighNoise
#SeniMelawanSepi
#TipisTapiPesta
#InternalkuBebas

𝐓𝐡𝐞 𝐂𝐚𝐬𝐚𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐨 𝐂𝐡𝐚𝐢𝐫, for us, 
is more than just a piece of furniture – 
it sets the tone, character, and hold historical value.

Back in 2018, 
the idea for Pulang was born at 
Bruges’ Dijver flea market. 
Hundreds of Casalino Chairs 
sparked a wild imagination of becoming 
“𝐨𝐧𝐞 𝐨𝐟 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐰𝐨𝐫𝐥𝐝’𝐬 𝐠𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐬𝐭 𝐡𝐨𝐭𝐞𝐥𝐬”

We can’t imagine how it would be like
without this chair.

A story.
A journey full of love.
12 days 4 hours.
3045 KM.
20,982 mtr climb.

Moving from one city to another, Adipati Bob discovers new experiences, new people, and the warmth he calls home. 

Happiness, relief, peace, struggle, uncertainty, and deep exhaustion are captured beautifully by @handiatma and @membacavisual in the movie “Sowan: 3000km around Java Island.”

caption:
Wahyu Santosa is a realism sculpture artist who depicts what’s inside his mind through his artwork.

His arts were inspired by something that became his most immense spirit; Indonesian culture. 

As realism disliked the romanticized portrayal of something, Wahyu portrays Indonesian culture as what it is through the sculpture of common citizens, people in the village, and local animals. Now, his artworks displayed in almost all Airports in Indonesia. 

One of his artwork placed in the lobby area to give a warm welcome to Pulang ke Uttara's customers.

So, what feels like home to you and why?
